See where to find width and height of the image : https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_bitmap

Original Size (second line, offset of 2 octets) :

width : 6e04
height : 3201

change height of it (since it is a large image) (add +2) : 3201 => 3203

dont forget to convert to visible format like png or jpg, use this command : $ mogrify -format jpg tunn3l_v1s10n.bmp

you should find the flag in tunn3l_v1s10n.jpg